The paper deals with the problem of extrinsic calibration between two sensors, which is a common problem in robotics and computer vision. The use of egomotion estimates suggests that the sensors are likely to be cameras or other visual sensors, which falls under the sub-categories of robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of optimization techniques and quadratic programming suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of theoretical results and analytical support suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
